The paper deals with natural language question answering, which is a subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of Markov Logic Networks (MLNs) suggests a focus on machine learning and probabilistic reasoning, which are also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of entity resolution methods, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
